{
  "title": "The Complete List of 2018 Risk All Star Winners",
  "author": "R&I Editorial Team",
  "date_published": "2018-09-14",
  "body": "<html><body><div class=\"contents\">\n<div class=\"avtempclass\" id=\"post-thumbnail\">\n<img alt=\"\" class=\"attachment-large size-large wp-post-image\" decoding=\"async\" fetchpriority=\"high\" height=\"525\" sizes=\"(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px\" src=\"https://riskandinsurance.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/09152018_AllStarsLogo_700x525-700x525.jpg\" srcset=\"https://riskandinsurance.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/09152018_AllStarsLogo_700x525.jpg 700w, https://riskandinsurance.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/09152018_AllStarsLogo_700x525-250x188.jpg 250w, https://riskandinsurance.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/09152018_AllStarsLogo_700x525-120x90.jpg 120w\" width=\"700\"/> </div>\n<h3><strong><a href=\"https://riskandinsurance.com/crisis-preparedness-at-its-best/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Crisis Preparedness at its Best</a> </strong></h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://riskandinsurance.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/09152018_1_AllStars_Queen150.jpg\"><img alt=\"\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-44910\" decoding=\"async\" height=\"150\" sizes=\"(max-width: 150px) 100vw, 150px\" src=\"https://riskandinsurance.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/09152018_1_AllStars_Queen150.jpg\" srcset=\"https://riskandinsurance.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/09152018_1_AllStars_Queen150.jpg 150w, https://riskandinsurance.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/09152018_1_AllStars_Queen150-120x120.jpg 120w\" width=\"150\"/></a>Elizabeth Queen, vice president of risk management, Wolters Kluwer</strong></p>\n<p>Elizabeth Queen led the development of a best-in-class incident management program that protects both employees and clients.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://riskandinsurance.com/protecting-those-who-care-for-kids/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Protecting Those Who Care for Kids</strong></a></h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://riskandinsurance.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/09152018_1_AllStars_Cady150.jpg\"><img alt=\"\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-44902\" decoding=\"async\" height=\"150\" sizes=\"(max-width: 150px) 100vw, 150px\" src=\"https://riskandinsurance.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/09152018_1_AllStars_Cady150.jpg\" srcset=\"https://riskandinsurance.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/09152018_1_AllStars_Cady150.jpg 150w, https://riskandinsurance.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/09152018_1_AllStars_Cady150-120x120.jpg 120w\" width=\"150\"/></a>Rebecca Cady, vice president, chief risk officer, Children’s National Medical Center</strong></p>\n<p>Rebecca Cady hard-wired communication into operations, allowing leaders to manage problems quickly and minimize litigation risk.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://riskandinsurance.com/the-lunch-pail-risk-manager/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>The ‘Lunch Pail’ Risk Manager</strong></a></h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://riskandinsurance.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/09152018_1_AllStars_Cunningham150.jpg\"><img alt=\"\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-44903\" decoding=\"async\" height=\"150\" loading=\"lazy\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 150px) 100vw, 150px\" src=\"https://riskandinsurance.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/09152018_1_AllStars_Cunningham150.jpg\" srcset=\"https://riskandinsurance.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/09152018_1_AllStars_Cunningham150.jpg 150w, https://riskandinsurance.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/09152018_1_AllStars_Cunningham150-120x120.jpg 120w\" width=\"150\"/></a>Jim Cunningham, vice president, risk management, Pinnacle Entertainment</strong></p>\n<p>Pinnacle’s Jim Cunningham earns the Risk All Star title for displaying a persistent, pragmatic approach to controlling losses.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://riskandinsurance.com/this-risk-taker-finds-a-passion-in-teaching-risk-management\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Risk Taker Teaches Risk Management</strong></a></h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://riskandinsurance.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/09152018_1_AllStars_Hampton150.jpg\"><img alt=\"\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-44906\" decoding=\"async\" height=\"150\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://riskandinsurance.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/09152018_1_AllStars_Hampton150.jpg\" width=\"150\"/></a>Jack Hampton, professor of business, director of graduate business programs, St. Peter’s University</strong></p>\n<p>Jack Hampton’s passion for making a difference is why the risk management program at Saint Peter’s University is thriving.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://riskandinsurance.com/fostering-seamless-acquisition/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Fostering Seamless Acquisition</strong></a></h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://riskandinsurance.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/09152018_1_AllStars_Bellone150.jpg\"><img alt=\"\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-44901\" decoding=\"async\" height=\"150\" loading=\"lazy\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 150px) 100vw, 150px\" src=\"https://riskandinsurance.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/09152018_1_AllStars_Bellone150.jpg\" srcset=\"https://riskandinsurance.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/09152018_1_AllStars_Bellone150.jpg 150w, https://riskandinsurance.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/09152018_1_AllStars_Bellone150-120x120.jpg 120w\" width=\"150\"/></a>Alumine Bellone, VP of risk management, Ardent Health Services</strong></p>\n<p>Alumine Bellone’s commitment to due diligence aided Ardent Health Services in a successful year of growth and acquisition.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://riskandinsurance.com/determined-to-protect-public-funds-this-risk-manager-found-out-of-the-box-solutions\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Saving the Public Purse</strong></a></h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://riskandinsurance.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/09152018_1_AllStars_Howard150.jpg\"><img alt=\"\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-44907\" decoding=\"async\" height=\"150\" loading=\"lazy\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 150px) 100vw, 150px\" src=\"https://riskandinsurance.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/09152018_1_AllStars_Howard150.jpg\" srcset=\"https://riskandinsurance.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/09152018_1_AllStars_Howard150.jpg 150w, https://riskandinsurance.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/09152018_1_AllStars_Howard150-120x120.jpg 120w\" width=\"150\"/></a>Dianne Howard, director of Benefits and Risk Management, Palm Beach County School District</strong></p>\n<p>Creativity and drive helped Dianne Howard find ways to protect thousands of schoolchildren without breaking the bank.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://riskandinsurance.com/this-las-vegas-risk-manager-eliminated-silos-redefining-risk-managements-role/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Silo-Busting, Meeting by Meeting</strong></a></h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://riskandinsurance.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/09152018_1_AllStars_Curbeam150.jpg\"><img alt=\"\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-44904\" decoding=\"async\" height=\"150\" loading=\"lazy\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 150px) 100vw, 150px\" src=\"https://riskandinsurance.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/09152018_1_AllStars_Curbeam150.jpg\" srcset=\"https://riskandinsurance.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/09152018_1_AllStars_Curbeam150.jpg 150w, https://riskandinsurance.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/09152018_1_AllStars_Curbeam150-120x120.jpg 120w\" width=\"150\"/></a>James Curbeam, risk manager, Las Vegas Valley Water District</strong></p>\n<p>James Curbeam knew the only way to achieve true ERM was by making every department aware of how their risks intertwined.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://riskandinsurance.com/miami-dade-risk-all-star/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Unifying Stakeholders to Drive Change</strong></a></h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://riskandinsurance.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/09152018_1_AllStars_Royo150.jpg\"><img alt=\"\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-44911\" decoding=\"async\" height=\"150\" loading=\"lazy\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 150px) 100vw, 150px\" src=\"https://riskandinsurance.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/09152018_1_AllStars_Royo150.jpg\" srcset=\"https://riskandinsurance.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/09152018_1_AllStars_Royo150.jpg 150w, https://riskandinsurance.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/09152018_1_AllStars_Royo150-120x120.jpg 120w\" width=\"150\"/></a>Rosa Royo, director, workers’ compensation, Miami-Dade County Public Schools</strong></p>\n<p>Rosa Royo discovered the ideal balance between controlling costs and providing high-quality care for injured workers.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://riskandinsurance.com/weathering-harvey/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Weathering Harvey</strong></a></h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://riskandinsurance.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/09152018_1_AllStars_Melnick150.jpg\"><img alt=\"\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-44908\" decoding=\"async\" height=\"150\" loading=\"lazy\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 150px) 100vw, 150px\" src=\"https://riskandinsurance.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/09152018_1_AllStars_Melnick150.jpg\" srcset=\"https://riskandinsurance.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/09152018_1_AllStars_Melnick150.jpg 150w, https://riskandinsurance.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/09152018_1_AllStars_Melnick150-120x120.jpg 120w\" width=\"150\"/></a>Craig Melnick, senior manager, risk management, Goodyear</strong></p>\n<p>Goodyear’s Craig Melnick used consistent communication and foresight to help his company rebound quickly from a major storm.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://riskandinsurance.com/this-risk-manager-put-critical-cat-data-at-the-industrys-fingertips\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Critical Cat Data at the Industry’s Fingertips</strong></a></h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://riskandinsurance.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/09152018_1_AllStars_Bank150.jpg\"><img alt=\"\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-44900\" decoding=\"async\" height=\"150\" loading=\"lazy\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 150px) 100vw, 150px\" src=\"https://riskandinsurance.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/09152018_1_AllStars_Bank150.jpg\" srcset=\"https://riskandinsurance.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/09152018_1_AllStars_Bank150.jpg 150w, https://riskandinsurance.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/09152018_1_AllStars_Bank150-120x120.jpg 120w\" width=\"150\"/></a>Ryan Bank, managing director, Geospatial Intelligence Center, National Insurance Crime Bureau</strong></p>\n<p>Ryan Bank leads a coalition that’s helping insurers and government agencies better understand severe weather risks.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://riskandinsurance.com/how-farm-life-shaped-a-tenacity-for-risk-management\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>How Farm Life Shaped a Tenacity for Risk Management</strong></a></h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://riskandinsurance.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/09152018_1_AllStars_Farthing150.jpg\"><img alt=\"\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-44905\" decoding=\"async\" height=\"150\" loading=\"lazy\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 150px) 100vw, 150px\" src=\"https://riskandinsurance.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/09152018_1_AllStars_Farthing150.jpg\" srcset=\"https://riskandinsurance.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/09152018_1_AllStars_Farthing150.jpg 150w, https://riskandinsurance.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/09152018_1_AllStars_Farthing150-120x120.jpg 120w\" width=\"150\"/></a>Kevin Farthing, environmental health and safety manager, Sparton Electronics</strong></p>\n<p>Growing up under the Kentucky sun trained Kevin Farthing for any risk and equipped him with a go-getter work ethic.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://riskandinsurance.com/when-faced-with-workers-comp-chaos-this-risk-manager-restructured-the-way-claims-were-handled\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Restructuring the Way Out of Claims Chaos</strong></a></h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://riskandinsurance.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/09152018_1_AllStars_Peck150.jpg\"><img alt=\"\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-44909\" decoding=\"async\" height=\"150\" loading=\"lazy\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 150px) 100vw, 150px\" src=\"https://riskandinsurance.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/09152018_1_AllStars_Peck150.jpg\" srcset=\"https://riskandinsurance.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/09152018_1_AllStars_Peck150.jpg 150w, https://riskandinsurance.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/09152018_1_AllStars_Peck150-120x120.jpg 120w\" width=\"150\"/></a>Kathleen Peck, director of risk management, MVP Staffing</strong></p>\n<p>For a staffing company with claims out of control, Kathleen Peck tore the program down and built it back up to achieve success.</p>\n<div class=\"bio\">The R&amp;I Editorial Team can be reached at <a class=\"__cf_email__\" data-cfemail=\"345951505d55575b5a4055574074405c515d5a47405d40414051471a5b4653\" href=\"/cdn-cgi/l/email-protection\">[email protected]</a>.</div>\n<div class=\"pad-1\"> </div>\n<div class=\"actions\">\n</div>\n</div></body></html>",
